description:
I am an experienced banking and finance lawyer with specialist expertise in:

• corporate and acquisition finance; 
• real estate and construction/development finance; and
• debt restructuring and corporate turnaround.

I have practised in Sydney, London and Milan, acting for many leading banks, debt funds, property funds, sponsors and other corporates in connection with their finance and restructuring needs.  I advise across a wide range of industries including agribusiness, retail, healthcare, construction and technology/start up businesses.  

Growing up in a family business and having invested time on secondment with a number of international investment banks, I understand the importance of customer satisfaction and I am responsive and empathetic to my clients needs.  My particular technical expertise includes drafting, negotiating/structuring and advising on:

• loan agreements (syndicated, club and bilateral);
• intercreditor arrangements, tripartite agreements and security documents; and
• standstill/forbearance arrangements and strategic turnaround activities.

A few examples of recent transactions I have acted on include advising:

• an Australian bank on a secured loan to a borrower for the acquisition and refinance of over 100 social and affordable housing units;

• a syndicate of banks on a secured loan facility to a borrowing group for corporate and working cap purposes in connection with its agri business; 

• a construction and development company on establishing a number of debt funds to invest in, and leverage returns on, its developments in the ACT and SA;

• a foreign investment bank on a senior secured loan to assist with the restructure of an Australian mining group; and

• a debt fund on secured loan facilities to developers to assist with the acquisition and development sites in NSW.

In 2018, I have also been a contributing author to the recently released “Banking & Finance” section of “Practical Law Australia” a Thomson Reuters publication.
